q) for vlan tagging, which is preferred: ISL or IEEE 802.1Q why:

 - IEEE 802.1Q is generally preferred for VLAN tagging over ISL (Inter-Switch Link)
due to several reasons:

Overall, IEEE 802.1Q is the preferred choice for VLAN tagging due to its standardization, compatibility, efficiency, scalability, and widespread adoption in the networking industry.

ISL is mostly deprecated now.
 - ISL there is problem with overhead as it adds 30 bytes to each frame.
 - IEEE 802.1Q adds only 4 bytes to each frame.
 - ISL is Cisco proprietary protocol.
 - IEEE 802.1Q is an open standard.
 - IEEE 802.1Q is supported by most of the networking vendors.
 - IEEE 802.1Q is more widely used in modern networks.
 - IEEE 802.1Q supports a larger number of VLANs (up to 4096) compared to ISL (up to 1024).